Bay Area Environmental Dashboard
Overview

This project is a mobile-ready web GIS dashboard that visualizes Bay Area county environmental patterns across time and space. 
It includes a choropleth/bivariate map, a county comparison bar chart, a time-series chart, 
and basic PWA support through a manifest and service worker.

Files Included
index.html
css/style.css
js/main.js
js/maps.js
js/charts.js
manifest.json
service-worker.js
data/ folder with CSV and GeoJSON files
icons/ folder with app icons
How to Run
Open the project folder in VS Code.
Start a local server using Live Server.
Open index.html in the browser through the local server.
For PWA testing, use Chrome and inspect the Application tab in DevTools.
Notes
The project is designed for desktop and mobile/narrow-screen use.
PWA behavior works best when served through localhost or HTTPS.
If service worker changes do not appear immediately, unregister the service worker and clear site storage in Chrome DevTools, then reload.
